job_description: Data Analyst - job post Albert Einstein College of Medicine 200 reviews 1300 Morris Park Ave, Bronx, NY 10461 Part-time Albert Einstein College of Medicine 200 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply on company site save-icon Job details Job Type Part-time POSITION RESPONSIBILITIES: The Data Analyst will be responsible for analyzing and supporting the databases. The individual will ensure all data is gathered, coded and analyzed, and that troubleshooting is performed . Manage analytic activities, reviewing, monitoring, and developing corrective action plan. Create and maintain a centralized database in which all study data will be stored. Manage data collection, analysis and cleaning, performing regular audits to ensure that the data collected are complete and accurate, and that the research is being conducted as outlined in the protocol. Assist PI with troubleshooting by running analyses, cleaning and preparing datasets. Partner with data resource center in the development of databases and data coding guidelines. Manage the collection of data from importable and exportable formats for rapid dissemination to PIs Manage additions/edits for all databases Perform other related duties as assigned. QUALIFICATIONS: Bachelor's Degree in Public health, epidemiology, biostatistics or related field and 1-2 years of related experience required. Master’s degree preferred. Strong working experience of MS Excel and statistical operations packages such as SPSS, STATA or R. Knowledge of statistical practices. Outstanding judgment, initiative, and attention to detail are essential. Can be relied upon to ensure that activities within areas of specific responsibility are completed in a timely manner. Ability to work well in a team setting and independently is essential.

You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply on company site save-icon Job details Job Type Part-time Job Description The Systems, Data, and Reporting for Enrollment Management team is seeking a curious and data-driven individual to assist with the analysis of undergraduate enrollment data to uncover trends across the enrollment cycle. The Part-Time Data Analyst Assistant will partner with members of the Enrollment Management team to analyze communication, event survey, and enrollment data with the main goal of finding patterns that may influence decision making. The Assistant should be thoughtful and highly organized, with an emphasis on ensuring confidentiality while working with prospective undergraduate student datasets. The Assistant will be fully trained in all areas needed to be successful in the role. This role is a part-time, hourly position and is remote. Students must have completed their undergraduate degree and must be currently enrolled in full-time graduate studies at Stevens. Must be available for up-to 20 hours per week from December 2022 through May 2023. Partner with the Enrollment Management Systems team; the primary responsibilities are, but not limited to: Complete training and onboarding of Technolutions Slate CRM Build and copy Slate queries and reports Analyze enrollment and survey data Compose abstracts/briefs to summarize findings Join bi-weekly team meetings, when available Required background Currently enrolled in a graduate degree program Bachelor’s degree required Experience manipulating and analyzing large datasets Proven track record of handling sensitive information with the highest level of professionalism and confidentiality Skills A keen eye toward uncovering trends Basic to intermediate modeling experience Ability to work independently and, at times, with limited supervision in a remote capacity Excellent written and oral communication skills are essential Strong interpersonal skills; proven capacity to communicate clearly Ability to think critically and to make sound recommendations SQL proficiency preferred Intermediate Excel proficiency Basic Word proficiency Department Admissions Operations General Submission Guidelines: In order to be considered a candidate for any job at Stevens, you must submit an online application. Business Analyst - Contact Center (Clinical Business Analyst) - job post NYC Health + Hospitals New York, NY 10004 $68,940 - $85,000 a year -  Full-time, Part-time Apply now Apply now save-icon Job details Salary $68,940 - $85,000 a year Job Type Full-time Part-time About NYC Health + Hospitals Empower Every New Yorker — Without Exception — to Live the Healthiest Life Possible NYC Health + Hospitals is the largest public health care system in the United States. We provide essential outpatient, inpatient and home-based services to more than one million New Yorkers every year across the city’s five boroughs. Our large health system consists of ambulatory centers, acute care centers, post-acute care/long-term care, rehabilitation programs, Home Care, and Correctional Health Services. Our diverse workforce is uniquely focused on empowering New Yorkers, without exception, to live the healthiest life possible. At NYC Health + Hospitals, our mission is to deliver high quality care health services, without exception. Every employee takes a person-centered approach that exemplifies the ICARE values (Integrity, Compassion, Accountability, Respect, and Excellence) through empathic communication and partnerships between all persons. Job Description Summary of Duties and Responsibilities: The New York City Health & Hospital’s Contact Center serves at the front line of our organization – often connecting patients to care as the first point of contact. We have a passionate and dedicated team focused on providing the best experience for our patients, Ambulatory Care facilities, and providers. Our team connects patients to needed medical services by partnering with leaders across the system to ensure an efficient and effective workflow is in place. We are also constantly working to improve our technological infrastructure to give patients the best options to communicate with us through their channel of choice. The Contact Center Business Analyst (Scripting and CRM) plays a key role in the maintenance, management and infrastructure of the Contact Center’s scripting tool. This individual will also act as an internal CRM representative for the Contact Center. In addition to collecting, analyzing and triaging updates, the Contact Center Business Analyst will also help prioritize critical changes and new requests. This individual will be expected to make strategic and efficiency recommendations to the stakeholders that align with the Contact Center and the organization’s goals. General tasks and responsibilities will include: Identify opportunities for streamlining business processes and improving the user experience Collaborate with multiple departments to build and maintain Contact Center call scripts Document changes within the scripting tool and engage vendor development team where appropriate Lead meetings and project presentations with stakeholders discussing and prioritizing changes, updates and new requests Perform Functional Testing, including script writing and test script execution Plan, coordinate, and support Functional Testing as well as User Acceptance Testing Represent the Contact Centers interest in the implementation of any new software or tools that impact scripting or Customer Relationship Management (CRM) Performs other related duties as assigned by Sr Director, Contact Center Shared Services or Sr Assist Vice President Minimum Qualifications 1. A Masters degree or advanced clinical degree from an accredited college or university and one (1) year of experience gathering and documenting business, clinical, and/or functional requirements using interviews, document analysis, workshops, surveys, site visits, business process descriptions, scenarios, business analysis, task and workflow analysis or related in a clinical, allied health, non-allied health, behavioral health, information technology, information services, business, analytics or related area; or, one (1) year of experience in a relevant clinical and/or healthcare administration role/function; or 2. A Baccalaureate degree from an accredited college or university and three (3) years of experience as described above; or 3. A satisfactory combination of education, training, and experience. 4. Specialty certification(s) issued by a national commercially available program, state, professional society, academic or technical institution in an area(s) listed above, may be credited on a month-to-month basis toward the required work experience for a total of one (1) year. Department Preferences Self-starter and ability to work independently. Strong organizational skills, meets deadlines and carries out duties efficiently. Successfully prioritizes competing tasks. Ability to troubleshoot and problem solve. Effective communication (written and oral). Ability to overcome organizational resistance to change. MS Office Suite – specifically Excel Visio Understanding of scripting decision trees Flow Chart experience Contact Center scripting tool functional experience preferably with Infinity or similar application. Project management Customer Relationship Management (CRM) Decision Tree software/tools NYC Health and Hospitals offers a competitive benefits package that includes: Comprehensive Health Benefits for employees hired to work 20+ hrs. per week Retirement Savings and Pension Plans Loan Forgiveness Programs for eligible employees Paid Holidays and Vacation in accordance with employees' Collectively bargained contracts College tuition discounts and professional development opportunities Multiple employee discounts programs Job Types: Full-time, Part-time Pay: $68,940.00 - $85,000.00 per year Benefits: 401(k) Dental insurance Flexible spending account Health insurance Paid holidays Paid sick time Paid time off Retirement plan Vision insurance Compensation package: Yearly pay Schedule: Day shift Work Location: One location Health insurance If you require alternative methods of application or screening, you must approach the employer directly to request this as Indeed is not responsible for the employer's application process.
